00:00:10.769 --> 00:00:13.769
winter arrives again. And the new year

00:00:13.769 --> 00:00:16.319
begins with the sound of rockets instead

00:00:16.319 --> 00:00:20.939
of fireworks. When you walk today, maybe

00:00:20.939 --> 00:00:22.259
you will pass one of your favorite

00:00:22.259 --> 00:00:25.769
buildings in Liverpool. What loss would

00:00:25.769 --> 00:00:31.289
you feel if it was no longer there? To

00:00:31.289 --> 00:00:33.179
walk through our streets now has become

00:00:33.179 --> 00:00:36.209
painful, physically painful to see the

00:00:36.209 --> 00:00:39.034
destruction of theaters, museums,

00:00:39.059 --> 00:00:41.189
libraries, churches, synagogues,

00:00:41.219 --> 00:00:43.679
mosques, you can recognize the

00:00:43.679 --> 00:00:45.989
historical face of a city through its

00:00:45.989 --> 00:00:50.309
buildings. You can't imagine how much

00:00:50.309 --> 00:00:54.844
heritage you will not manage to rebuild.

00:00:54.869 --> 00:00:56.819
cherished memories in our favorite

00:00:56.819 --> 00:01:01.619
places are now scarred as joy from the

00:01:01.619 --> 00:01:17.015
past becomes distorted in the present.

00:01:17.040 --> 00:01:20.700
Time stopped and he doesn't move any

00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:25.235
more. Time was short with air bombs.

00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:28.230
